$ Windows NT

In 1988, Microsoft hired *Dave Cutler* (the creator of DEC's VAX/VMS OS) to create an OS for Microsoft: Windows NT.

Windows NT became the foundation for Windows 2000, Windows XP, Windows Visat, Windos 7, Windows 8 and
→ Windows/versions/10[Windows 10].

A specific architectural goal of Windows NT were the → Windows/development/Portable-Executable/subsystem[subsystems].

Because at the time of designing Windows NT, Object Oriented languages were on the rise, in Windows NT, everything is an object (as opposed to
→ Linux, where everythying is a file).
